node.text:
S.O.S.
SAVE OUR SHOP 
It is difficult to ask for help, but YOU are the only one who can help us.    —If we are more to you than just a business, please let the city of Austin and our landlord know.
 Without you, our community, we would not be here in the first place.

  If you email today your voice will be heard at the city review on Monday
  to help: email(by midnight tonight 7/24) preservation@austintexas.gov
  SUBJECT: save No-Comply, oppose demolition of 812 W. 12th st

  A permit for demolition has been filed!
There is a city review on Monday to consider issuing a permit, postponement of permit, or designating as a historical landmark and never issuing a demolition permit.  
  If you also want to speak on our behalf, email ( SUBJECT speak for saving No-Comply) and you will be called upon during the zoom meeting: 7/26 6pm austintexas.gov/HLC
  We love our building and would love to stay; but if we have to leave, we at least need more time to find a new place that works for our community.
